      • getFiles

        java.util.Set<FileEntity> getFiles(@NotNull
                                   @NotNull java.util.Set<java.lang.String> files)
        Get all the file entity references that match the input set of file strings.
        Parameters:
        files - the file strings to search for
        Returns:
        The set of files entities found. Note: if a file in files doesn't exist in database the set returned will consist of all other discovered files. E.G. files is ("a", "b", "c") and only "b" and "c" are in the database the returned set will contain "b" and "c". The method won't fail.
